					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-440666#post-1368108</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-440666/scp-1201#post-1368108</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 07 Feb 2012 07:21:15 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Anaxagoras</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1019930</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Come to think of it, why even maintain a constant perimeter? The well seems non-anomalous outside of that one yearly incident, so it seems like they can let people at least kinda close most of the time. Monitor it, sure, but a full-scale exclusion zone is more effort than is probably needed, especially in the middle of a city.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-440666#post-1368104</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-440666/scp-1201#post-1368104</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 07 Feb 2012 07:09:24 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Khym Chanur</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>163438</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>A few critiques:</p> <ol> <li>You seem to sometimes use &quot;SCP-1201&quot; to mean the well, and sometimes to mean the area around the well. I think you should call the well &quot;SP-1201-1&quot;, and use &quot;SCP-1201&quot; for the area around the well.</li> <li>To keep a 50m perimeter around the well at all times, the Foundation is going to need to have some excuse to keep all civilians out of it without letting on that anything is weird is going on. Maybe buy up all the property in the area and turn it into a warehouse.</li> </ol> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
